{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "notes": [
    "Per-SKU platform registry: public identity (vendor/arch/machine/product), fixed",
    "placement (gpus_per_node, scale_up_domain, scale_up_transport), launcher, the",
    "operator-config fields the SKU requires, and canonical runtime policy",
    "(run_timeout, optional master_port). capability.py derives the EP topologies",
    "from these values; suites.yaml 'platforms: all' resolves to every SKU listed",
    "here; runtime/config.py derives its operator-config schema and canonical policy from them.",
    "The optional 'network' block carries the SKU's operator-approved scale-out RDMA",
    "selectors, overlaid onto the base operator config by runtime/config.py.",
    "The optional per-SKU 'operator' block is the tracked baseline for runner-local",
    "settings (placement, dirs, exclude lists) - de-secreted by operator decision",
    "2026-07-12 from live cluster state and a recovered manual config. An operator",
    "config file/secret, when present, overrides these per field. audit_salt and",
    "any value not listed here remain secret. Pending blocks (still secret-fed):",
    "gb200 (no SSH path), mi300x/mi325x (cluster unreachable at derivation time);",
    "b300 stage_dir and gb300 squash_dir/enroot_cache_path were not recoverable."
  ],
